Perfecta Relación lineal: a partir del valor de x, podemos predecir con exactitud el valor que asumirá y.
Por ejemplo, si compramos tal cantidad de productos, podemos definir con exactitud el precio que pagaremos


Definición de Regresión Lineal
Linear regression is the statistical method for fitting a line to data where the relationship
between two variables, x and y, can be modeled by a straight line with some error:

y= β0 + β1x+ ε
The values β0 and β1 represent the model’s parameters (β is the Greek letter beta), and the error is
represented by ε(the Greek letter epsilon). The parameters are estimated using data, and we write
their point estimates as b0 and b1. When we use xto predict y, we usually call xthe explanatory or
predictor variable, and we call y the response; we also often drop the ϵ term when writing down
the model since our main focus is often on the prediction of the average outcome.
Incluir fórmula residual

subestima: residual positivo, sobreestima: negativo


